An ailing man has been beaten to death by his cousin in Nyahera Kisumu county. The deceased George Juma, 28, was allegedly hit with a blunt object by Jack Abongo,30. Kisumu West OCPD Meshack Kiptum told the Star on the phone that the two men had quarrelled before a fight ensued around 2.00 am. Abongo escaped after the incident. Police are looking for him. Angry residents attacked the suspect's home and burnt his two houses. The body of the deceased was taken to Jaramogi Oginga Odinga Teaching and Referral Morgue. Click here for the latest political news